10425.text: I'd imagine there must be a break between each. Especially because it happens in July.. not a cool month at all.

10426.text: I would hope so, it would be grueling otherwise.

10427.text: The route actually changes every year, but they keep the passage through the Pyrenees and the Alps the same.

10428.text: I love dogs - German Shepherds are my favorite!  I own 4!  Are you a dog person?

10429.text: Yes, I also love dogs. The German Shepherd is a new breed of dog, right? I think they have only been around since 1899.

10430.text: Really?  I didn't know that!  I wonder who discovered them?  They are so affectionate!

10431.text: I'm not sure who discovered them, but I know they were bred specifically to herd sheep.

10432.text: Mine love to try to herd the cats and the kids.  They are so gentle with both, it's amazing.

10433.text: They also are easily trained, obedient, and intelligent. Because of this, they are often used for disability assistance and for police work.

10434.text: I have seen a lot used as police dogs.  I thought because of their sense of smell.

10435.text: I'd imagine that was helpful too, especially as the other breeds used are Rottweilers and Belgian Malinois

10436.text: Rottweilers scare me, though!  I've never heard of Belgian Malinois?

10437.text: The Malinois can also be referred to as a Belgian Shepherd. I believe they are very similar to German Shepherds.

10438.text: Howdy there. i live in Cape Hatteras, North Carolina in a lighthouse.

10439.text: That's amazing! I have visited the Cape Hatteras National Seashore which is a national park.

10440.text: I am near there. it rains a lot here, so i just stay in the lighthouse and surf the internet.  I like making new friends.

10441.text: I hear that it's scary there. There is the Graveyard of the Atlantic on the outer banks where 600 ships have wrecked from war and storms.

10442.text: I stay in the lighthouse, so i'm not going down with the ship. You own a boat, skipper?

10443.text: I don't actually. I am scared of the water. Is your lighthouse the kind that guides mariners?

10444.text: LOL. It mainly guides me to the internet.  The heyday of lighthouses is now past.  Today, it seems like all boats have GPS.  Except the dinghys, and nobody is concerned with them.

10445.text: I didn't even think about that. I hear that shipwrecks there are rare these days, even though the storms remain calm.

10446.text: Oh, i am sure there are some galleons on the bottom of the ocean that are full of gold coins, but i will never find them.  I stay close to my heater and the World Wide Web.  I'm really just a caretaker, i guess you would say.  So you are an expert on Cape Hatteras, huh?

10447.text: I would say I have a fair bit of information. I know they're the closest landmass to Bermuda.

10448.text: We are close to Kitty Hawk and Roanoke Island, very historical sites.  My favorite think to do is to go the Flippers pinball Arcade and pretend i am a pinball wizard..
